When Harry, Ron, and Hermione entered the Great Hall for breakfast the next day, the first thing they saw was Draco Malfoy, who seemed to be entertaining a large group of Slytherins with a very funny story. As they passed, Malfoy did a ridiculous impression of a swooning fit and there was a roar of laughter.\par
\ldblquote Ignore him,\rdblquote  said Hermione, who was right behind Harry. \ldblquote Just ignore him, it\rquote s not worth it. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hey, Potter!\rdblquote  shrieked Pansy Parkinson, a Slytherin girl with a face like a pug. \ldblquote Potter! The dementors are coming, Potter! \i Woooooooo\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry dropped into a seat at the Gryffindor table, next to George Weasley.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote New third-year course schedules,\rdblquote  said George, passing them over. \ldblquote What\rquote s up with you, Harry?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Malfoy,\rdblquote  said Ron, sitting down on George\rquote s other side and glaring over at the Slytherin table.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 George looked up in time to see Malfoy pretending to faint with terror again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That little git,\rdblquote  he said calmly. \ldblquote He wasn\rquote t so cocky last night when the dementors were down at our end of the train. Came run\-ning into our compartment, didn\rquote t he, Fred?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Nearly wet himself,\rdblquote  said Fred, with a contemptuous glance at Malfoy.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I wasn\rquote t too happy myself,\rdblquote  said George. \ldblquote They\rquote re horrible things, those dementors. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Sort of freeze your insides, don\rquote t they?\rdblquote  said Fred.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You didn\rquote t pass out, though, did you?\rdblquote  said Harry in a low voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Forget it, Harry,\rdblquote  said George bracingly. \ldblquote Dad had to go out to Azkaban one time, remember, Fred? And he said it was the worst place he\rquote d ever been, he came back all weak and shaking. \'85 They suck the happiness out of a place, dementors. Most of the prison\-ers go mad in there.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Anyway, we\rquote ll see how happy Malfoy looks after our first Quid\-ditch match,\rdblquote  said Fred. \ldblquote Gryffindor versus Slytherin, first game of the season, remember?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The only time Harry and Malfoy had faced each other in a Quidditch match, Malfoy had definitely come off worse. Feeling slightly more cheerful, Harry helped himself to sausages and fried tomatoes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione was examining her new schedule.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ooh, good, we\rquote re starting some new subjects today,\rdblquote  she said happily.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hermione,\rdblquote  said Ron, frowning as he looked over her shoulder, \ldblquote they\rquote ve messed up your schedule. Look \emdash  they\rquote ve got you down for about ten subjects a day. There isn\rquote t enough \i time.\i0\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote ll manage. I\rquote ve fixed it all with Professor McGonagall.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But look,\rdblquote  said Ron, laughing, \ldblquote see this morning? Nine o\rquote clock, Divination. And underneath, nine o\rquote clock, Muggle Studies. And\rdblquote  \emdash  Ron leaned closer to the schedule, disbelieving \emdash  \ldblquote\i look\i0  \emdash  underneath that, Arithmancy, \i nine o\rquote clock.\i0  I mean, I know you\rquote re good, Hermione, but no one\rquote s \i that\i0  good. How\rquote re you supposed to be in three classes at once?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t be silly,\rdblquote  said Hermione shortly. \ldblquote Of course I won\rquote t be in three classes at once.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, then \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Pass the marmalade,\rdblquote  said Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, Ron, what\rquote s it to you if my schedule\rquote s a bit full?\rdblquote  Hermione snapped. \ldblquote I told you, I\rquote ve fixed it all with Professor McGonagall.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Just then, Hagrid entered the Great Hall. He was wearing his long moleskin overcoat and was absentmindedly swinging a dead polecat from one enormous hand.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote All righ\rquote ?\rdblquote  he said eagerly, pausing on the way to the staff table. \ldblquote Yer in my firs\rquote  ever lesson! Right after lunch! Bin up since five gettin\rquote  everythin\rquote  ready. \'85 Hope it\rquote s okay. \'85 Me, a teacher \'85 hones\rquote ly. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He grinned broadly at them and headed off to the staff table, still swinging the polecat.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Wonder what he\rquote s been getting ready?\rdblquote  said Ron, a note of anx\-iety in his voice.\par
The hall was starting to empty as people headed off toward their first lesson. Ron checked his course schedule.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We\rquote d better go, look, Divination\rquote s at the top of North Tower. It\rquote ll take us ten minutes to get there. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They finished their breakfasts hastily, said good-bye to Fred and George, and walked back through the hall. As they passed the Slytherin table, Malfoy did yet another impression of a faint\-ing fit. The shouts of laughter followed Harry into the entrance hall.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The journey through the castle to North Tower was a long one. Two years at Hogwarts hadn\rquote t taught them everything about the castle, and they had never been inside North Tower before.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There\rquote s \emdash  got \emdash  to \emdash  be \emdash  a \emdash  shortcut,\rdblquote  Ron panted as they climbed their seventh long staircase and emerged on an unfa\-miliar landing, where there was nothing but a large painting of a bare stretch of grass hanging on the stone wall.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I think it\rquote s this way,\rdblquote  said Hermione, peering down the empty passage to the right.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Can\rquote t be,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote That\rquote s south, look, you can see a bit of the lake out of the window \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry was watching the painting. A fat, dapple-gray pony had just ambled onto the grass and was grazing nonchalantly. Harry was used to the subjects of Hogwarts paintings moving around and leaving their frames to visit one another, but he always enjoyed watching it. A moment later, a short, squat knight in a suit of ar\-mor clanked into the picture after his pony. By the look of the grass stains on his metal knees, he had just fallen off.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Aha!\rdblquote  he yelled, seeing Harry, Ron, and Hermione. \ldblquote What\lang3081  \lang1033 villains are these, that trespass upon my private lands! Come to scorn at my fall, perchance? Draw, you knaves, you dogs!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They watched in astonishment as the little knight tugged his sword out of its scabbard and began brandishing it violently, hop\-ping up and down in rage. But the sword was too long for him; a particularly wild swing made him overbalance, and he landed face\-down in the grass.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Are you all right?\rdblquote  said Harry, moving closer to the picture.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Get back, you scurvy braggart! Back, you rogue!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The knight seized his sword again and used it to push himself back up, but the blade sank deeply into the grass and, though he pulled with all his might, he couldn\rquote t get it out again. Finally, he had to flop back down onto the grass and push up his visor to mop his sweating face.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Listen,\rdblquote  said Harry, taking advantage of the knight\rquote s exhaus\-tion, \ldblquote we\rquote re looking for the North Tower. You don\rquote t know the way, do you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
