\lang1033\ldblquote Well \'85 when you fell off, it got blown away,\rdblquote  said Hermione hesitantly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And it hit \emdash  it hit \emdash  oh, Harry \emdash  it hit the Whomping Wil\-low.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry\rquote s insides lurched. The Whomping Willow was a very vio\-lent tree that stood alone in the middle of the grounds.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And?\rdblquote  he said, dreading the answer.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, you know the Whomping Willow,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote It \emdash  it doesn\rquote t like being hit.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Professor Flitwick brought it back just before you came around,\rdblquote  said Hermione in a very small voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Slowly, she reached down for a bag at her feet, turned it upside down, and tipped a dozen bits of splintered wood and twig onto the bed, the only remains of Harry\rquote s faithful, finally beaten broom\-stick.\lang3081\par
