Why had nobody ever told him? Dumbledore, Hagrid, Mr. Weasley, Cornelius Fudge \'85 why hadn\rquote t anyone ever mentioned the fact that Harry\rquote s parents had died because their best friend had betrayed them?\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron and Hermione watched Harry nervously all through din\-ner, not daring to talk about what they\rquote d overheard, because Percy was sitting close by them. When they went upstairs to the crowded common room, it was to find Fred and George had set off half a dozen Dungbombs in a fit of end-of-term high spirits. Harry, who didn\rquote t want Fred and George asking him whether he\rquote d reached\lang3081  \lang1033 Hogsmeade or not, sneaked quietly up to the empty dormitory and headed straight for his bedside cabinet. He pushed his books aside and quickly found what he was looking for \emdash  the leather-bound photo album Hagrid had given him two years ago, which was full of wizard pictures of his mother and father. He sat down on his bed, drew the hangings around him, and started turning the pages, searching, until\lang3081  \lang1033\'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He stopped on a picture of his parents\rquote  wedding day. There was his father waving up at him, beaming, the untidy black hair Harry had inherited standing up in all directions. There was his mother, alight with happiness, arm in arm with his dad. And there \'85 that must be him. Their best man \'85 Harry had never given him a thought before.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 If he hadn\rquote t known it was the same person, he would never have guessed it was Black in this old photograph. His face wasn\rquote t sunken and waxy, but handsome, full of laughter. Had he already been working for Voldemort when this picture had been taken? Was he already planning the deaths of the two people next to him? Did he realize he was facing twelve years in Azkaban, twelve years that would make him unrecognizable?\lang3081\par
\lang1033\i But the dementors don\rquote t affect him,\i0  Harry thought, staring into the handsome, laughing face. \i He doesn\rquote t have to hear my mum screaming if they get too close\i0  \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry slammed the album shut, reached over and stuffed it back into his cabinet, took off his robe and glasses and got into bed, making sure the hangings were hiding him from view.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The dormitory door opened.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry?\rdblquote  said Ron\rquote s voice uncertainly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But Harry lay still, pretending to be asleep. He heard Ron leave again, and rolled over on his back, his eyes wide open.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A hatred such as he had never known before was coursing through Harry like poison. He could see Black laughing at him through the darkness, as though somebody had pasted the picture from the album over his eyes. He watched, as though somebody was playing him a piece of film, Sirius Black blasting Peter Petti\-grew (who resembled Neville Longbottom) into a thousand pieces. He could hear (though having no idea what Black\rquote s voice might sound like) a low, excited mutter. \ldblquote It has happened, My Lord \'85 the Potters have made me their Secret-Keeper. \'85\rdblquote  And then came another voice, laughing shrilly, the same laugh that Harry heard inside his head whenever the dementors drew near. \'85\lang3081\par
