\lang1033 They turned into the corridor to Gryffindor Tower and saw Neville Longbottom, pleading with Sir Cadogan, who seemed to be refusing him entrance.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I wrote them down!\rdblquote  Neville was saying tearfully. \ldblquote But I must\rquote ve dropped them somewhere!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote A likely tale!\rdblquote  roared Sir Cadogan. Then, spotting\lang3081  \lang1033 Harry and Ron: \ldblquote Good even, my fine young yeomen! Come clap this loon in irons. He is trying to force entry to the chambers within!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, shut up,\rdblquote  said Ron as he and Harry drew level with Neville.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote ve lost the passwords!\rdblquote  Neville told them miserably. \ldblquote I made him tell me what passwords he was going to use this week, because he keeps changing them, and now I don\rquote t know what I\rquote ve done with them!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oddsbodikins,\rdblquote  said Harry to Sir Cadogan, who looked ex\-tremely disappointed and reluctantly swung forward to let them into the common room. There was a sudden, excited murmur as every head turned and the next moment, Harry was surrounded by people exclaiming over his Firebolt.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Where\rquote d you get it, Harry?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Will you let me have a go?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Have you ridden it yet, Harry?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ravenclaw\rquote ll have no chance, they\rquote re all on Cleansweep Sevens!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Can I just \i hold\i0  it, Harry?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 After ten minutes or so, during which the Firebolt was passed around and admired from every angle, the crowd dispersed and Harry and Ron had a clear view of Hermione, the only person who hadn\rquote t rushed over to them, bent over her work and carefully avoid\-ing their eyes. Harry and Ron approached her table and at last, she looked up.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I got it back,\rdblquote  said Harry, grinning at her and holding up the Firebolt.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote See, Hermione? There wasn\rquote t anything wrong with it!\rdblquote  said Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well \emdash  there \i might\i0  have been!\rdblquote  said Hermione. \ldblquote I mean, at least you know now that it\rquote s safe!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, I suppose so,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote I\rquote d better put it upstairs \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote ll take it!\rdblquote  said Ron eagerly. \ldblquote I\rquote ve got to give Scabbers his rat tonic.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He took the Firebolt and, holding it as if it were made of glass, carried it away up the boys\rquote  staircase.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Can I sit down, then?\rdblquote  Harry asked Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I suppose so,\rdblquote  said Hermione, moving a great stack of parch\-ment off a chair.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry looked around at the cluttered table, at the long Arith\-mancy essay on which the ink was still glistening, at the even longer Muggle Studies essay (\lang3081\ldblquote\lang1033 Explain Why Muggles Need Electricity\lang3081\rdblquote\lang1033 ) and at the rune translation Hermione was now poring over.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How are you getting through all this stuff?\rdblquote  Harry asked her.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, well \emdash  you know \emdash  working hard,\rdblquote  said Hermione. Close-up, Harry saw that she looked almost as tired as Lupin.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Why don\rquote t you just drop a couple of subjects?\rdblquote  Harry asked, watching her lifting books as she searched for her rune dictionary.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I couldn\rquote t do that!\rdblquote  said Hermione, looking scandalized.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Arithmancy looks terrible,\rdblquote  said Harry, picking up a very com\-plicated-looking number chart.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh no, it\rquote s wonderful!\rdblquote  said Hermione earnestly. \ldblquote It\rquote s my fa\-vorite subject! It\rquote s \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But exactly what was wonderful about Arithmancy, Harry never found out. At that precise moment, a strangled yell echoed down the boys\rquote  staircase. The whole common room fell silent, staring, petrified, at the entrance. Then came hurried footsteps, growing louder and louder \emdash  and then Ron came leaping into view, drag\-ging with him a bedsheet.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote LOOK!\rdblquote  he bellowed, striding over to Hermione\rquote s table. \ldblquote LOOK!\rdblquote  he yelled, shaking the sheets in her face.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ron, what \emdash  ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote SCABBERS! LOOK! SCABBERS!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione was leaning away from Ron, looking utterly bewil\-dered. Harry looked down at the sheet Ron was holding. There was something red on it. Something that looked horribly like \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote BLOOD!\rdblquote  Ron yelled into the stunned silence. \ldblquote HE\rquote S GONE! AND YOU KNOW WHAT WAS ON THE FLOOR?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote N \emdash  no,\rdblquote  said Hermione in a trembling voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron threw something down onto Hermione\rquote s rune translation. Hermione and Harry leaned forward. Lying on top of the weird, spiky shapes were several long, ginger cat hairs.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\par
