\lang1033 Harry felt a nasty pang of guilt. He had completely forgotten that Buckbeak\rquote s trial was so near, and judging by the uneasy look on Ron\rquote s face, he had too. They had also forgotten their promise about helping him prepare Buckbeak\rquote s defense; the arrival of the Firebolt had driven it clean out of their minds.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hagrid poured them tea and offered them a plate of Bath buns, but they knew better than to accept; they had had too much expe\-rience with Hagrid\rquote s cooking.\lang3081\par
