\lang1033 Wood paced the field, staring around with the team behind him. Finally, they saw the front doors of the castle open in the distance and the rest of the school spilling onto the lawn.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Locker rooms,\rdblquote  said Wood tersely.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 None of them spoke as they changed into their scarlet robes. Harry wondered if they were feeling like he was: as though he\rquote d eaten something extremely wriggly for breakfast. In what seemed like no time at all, Wood was saying, \ldblquote Okay, it\rquote s time, let\rquote s go \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They walked out onto the field to a tidal wave of noise. Three-quarters of the crowd was wearing scarlet rosettes, waving scarlet flags with the Gryffindor lion upon them, or brandishing banners with slogans like \ldblquote GO GRYFFINDOR!\rdblquote  and \ldblquote LIONS FOR THE CUP!\rdblquote  Behind the Slytherin goal posts, however, two hundred people were wearing green; the silver serpent of Slytherin glittered on their flags, and Professor Snape sat in the very front row, wear\-ing green like everyone else, and a very grim smile.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And here are the Gryffindors!\rdblquote  yelled Lee Jordan, who was act\-ing as commentator as usual. \ldblquote Potter, Bell, Johnson, Spinnet, Weasley, Weasley, and Wood. Widely acknowledged as the best team Hogwarts has seen in a good few years \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Lee\rquote s comments were drowned by a tide of \ldblquote boos\rdblquote  from the Slytherin end.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And here come the Slytherin team, led by Captain Flint. He\rquote s made some changes in the lineup and seems to be going for size rather than skill \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 More boos from the Slytherin crowd. Harry, however, thought\lang3081  \lang1033 Lee had a point. Malfoy was easily the smallest person on the Slytherin team; the rest of them were enormous.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Captains, shake hands!\rdblquote  said Madam Hooch.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Flint and Wood approached each other and grasped each other\rquote s hand very tightly; it looked as though each was trying to break the other\rquote s fingers.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Mount your brooms!\rdblquote  said Madam Hooch. \ldblquote Three \'85 two \'85 one\lang3081  \lang1033\'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The sound of her whistle was lost in the roar from the crowd as fourteen brooms rose into the air. Harry felt his hair fly back off his forehead; his nerves left him in the thrill of the flight; he glanced around, saw Malfoy on his tail, and sped off in search of the Snitch.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And it\rquote s Gryffindor in possession, Alicia Spinnet of Gryffindor with the Quaffle, heading straight for the Slytherin goal posts, looking good, Alicia! Argh, no \emdash  Quaffle intercepted by Warring\-ton, Warrington of Slytherin tearing up the field \emdash  WHAM! \emdash  nice Bludger work there by George Weasley, Warrington drops the Quaffle, it\rquote s caught by \emdash  Johnson, Gryffindor back in possession, come on, Angelina \emdash  nice swerve around Montague \emdash  \i duck, An\-gelina, that\rquote s a Bludger\i0 !\lang3081  \lang1033\emdash\lang3081  \lang1033 SHE SCORES! TEN\lang3081\endash\lang1033 ZERO TO GRYFFINDOR!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Angelina punched the air as she soared around the end of the field; the sea of scarlet below was screaming its delight \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote OUCH!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Angelina was nearly thrown from her broom as Marcus Flint went smashing into her.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Sorry!\rdblquote  said Flint as the crowd below booed. \ldblquote Sorry, didn\rquote t see her!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A moment later, Fred Weasley chucked his Beater\rquote s club at the back of Flint\rquote s head. Flint\rquote s nose smashed into the handle of his broom and began to bleed.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That will do!\rdblquote  shrieked Madam Hooch, zooming between them. \ldblquote Penalty shot to Gryffindor for an unprovoked attack on their Chaser! Penalty shot to Slytherin for deliberate damage to \i their\i0  Chaser!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Come off it, Miss!\rdblquote  howled Fred, but Madam Hooch blew her whistle and Alicia flew forward to take the penalty.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Come on, Alicia!\rdblquote  yelled Lee into the silence that had de\-scended on the crowd. \ldblquote YES! SHE\rquote S BEATEN THE KEEPER! TWENTY\lang3081\endash\lang1033 ZERO TO GRYFFINDOR!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry turned the Firebolt sharply to watch Flint, still bleeding freely, fly forward to take the Slytherin penalty. Wood was hovering in front of the Gryffindor goal posts, his jaw clenched.\lang3081\par
\ldblquote  \rquote\lang1033 Course, Wood\rquote s a superb Keeper!\rdblquote  Lee Jordan told the crowd as Flint waited for Madam Hooch\rquote s whistle. \ldblquote Superb! Very difficult to pass \emdash  very difficult indeed \emdash  YES! I DON\rquote T BELIEVE IT! HE\rquote S SAVED IT!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Relieved, Harry zoomed away, gazing around for the Snitch, but still making sure he caught every word of Lee\rquote s commentary. It was essential that he hold Malfoy off the Snitch until Gryffindor was more than fifty points up \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Gryffindor in possession, no, Slytherin in possession \emdash  no! \emdash  Gryffindor back in possession and it\rquote s Katie Bell, Katie Bell for Gryffindor with the Quaffle, she\rquote s streaking up the field \emdash  THAT WAS DELIBERATE!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Montague, a Slytherin Chaser, had swerved in front of Katie,\lang3081  \lang1033 and instead of seizing the Quaffle had grabbed her head. Katie cart\-wheeled in the air, managed to stay on her broom, but dropped the Quaffle.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Madam Hooch\rquote s whistle rang out again as she soared over to Montague and began shouting at him. A minute later, Katie had put another penalty past the Slytherin Seeker.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote THIRTY\lang3081\endash\lang1033 ZERO! TAKE THAT, YOU DIRTY, CHEAT\-ING \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Jordan, if you can\rquote t commentate in an unbiased way \emdash  !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m telling it like it is, Professor!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry felt a huge jolt of excitement. He had seen the Snitch \emdash  it was shimmering at the foot of one of the Gryffindor goal posts \emdash  but he mustn\rquote t catch it yet \emdash  and if Malfoy saw it \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Faking a look of sudden concentration, Harry pulled his Fire\-bolt around and sped off toward the Slytherin end \emdash  it worked. Malfoy went haring after him, clearly thinking Harry had seen the Snitch there. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 WHOOSH.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 One of the Bludgers came streaking past Harry\rquote s right ear, hit by the gigantic Slytherin Beater, Derrick. Then again \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 WHOOSH.\lang3081\par
