\lang1033 Harry had a fleeting glimpse of Bole and Derrick zooming toward him, clubs raised \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He turned the Firebolt upward at the last second, and Bole and Derrick collided with a sickening crunch.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ha haaa!\rdblquote  yelled Lee Jordan as the Slytherin Beaters lurched away from each other, clutching their heads. \ldblquote Too bad, boys! You\rquote ll\lang3081  \lang1033 need to get up earlier than that to beat a Firebolt! And it\rquote s Gryf\-findor in possession again, as Johnson takes the Quaffle \emdash  Flint alongside her \emdash  poke him in the eye, Angelina! \emdash  it was a joke, Professor, it was a joke \emdash  oh no \emdash  Flint in possession, Flint flying toward the Gryffindor goal posts, come on now, Wood, save \emdash  !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But Flint had scored; there was an eruption of cheers from the Slytherin end, and Lee swore so badly that Professor McGonagall tried to tug the magical megaphone away from him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Sorry, Professor, sorry! Won\rquote t happen again! So, Gryffindor in the lead, thirty points to ten, and Gryffindor in possession \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It was turning into the dirtiest game Harry had ever played in. Enraged that Gryffindor had taken such an early lead, the Slytherins were rapidly resorting to any means to take the Quaffle. Bole hit Alicia with his club and tried to say he\rquote d thought she was a Bludger. George Weasley elbowed Bole in the face in retalia\-tion. Madam Hooch awarded both teams penalties, and Wood pulled off another spectacular save, making the score forty-ten to Gryffindor.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The Snitch had disappeared again. Malfoy was still keeping close to Harry as he soared over the match, looking around for it \emdash  once Gryffindor was fifty points ahead \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Katie scored. Fifty-ten. Fred and George Weasley were swoop\-ing around her, clubs raised, in case any of the Slytherins were thinking of revenge. Bole and Derrick took advantage of Fred\rquote s and George\rquote s absence to aim both Bludgers at Wood; they caught him in the stomach, one after the other, and he rolled over in the air, clutching his broom, completely winded.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Madam Hooch was beside herself.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote YOU DO NOT ATTACK THE KEEPER UNLESS THE\lang3081  \lang1033 QUAFFLE IS WITHIN THE SCORING AREA!\rdblquote  she shrieked at Bole and Derrick. \ldblquote Gryffindor penalty!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And Angelina scored. Sixty-ten. Moments later, Fred Weasley pelted a Bludger at Warrington, knocking the Quaffle out of his hands; Alicia seized it and put it through the Slytherin goal \emdash  seventy-ten.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The Gryffindor crowd below was screaming itself hoarse \emdash  Gryffindor was sixty points in the lead, and if Harry caught the Snitch now, the Cup was theirs. Harry could almost feel hundreds of eyes following him as he soared around the field, high above the rest of the game, with Malfoy speeding along behind him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And then he saw it. The Snitch was sparkling twenty feet above him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry put on a huge burst of speed; the wind was roaring in his ears; he stretched out his hand, but suddenly, the Firebolt was slow\-ing down \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Horrified, he looked around. Malfoy had thrown himself for\-ward, grabbed hold of the Firebolt\rquote s tail, and was pulling it back.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry was angry enough to hit Malfoy, but couldn\rquote t reach \emdash  Malfoy was panting with the effort of holding onto the Firebolt, but his eyes were sparkling maliciously. He had achieved what he\rquote d wanted to do \emdash  the Snitch had disappeared again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Penalty! Penalty to Gryffindor! I\rquote ve never seen such tactics!\rdblquote  Madam Hooch screeched, shooting up to where Malfoy was slid\-ing back onto his Nimbus Two Thousand and One.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote YOU CHEATING SCUM!\rdblquote  Lee Jordan was howling into the megaphone, dancing out of Professor McGonagall\rquote s reach. \ldblquote YOU FILTHY, CHEATING B \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Professor McGonagall didn\rquote t even bother to tell him off. She was actually shaking her finger in Malfoy\rquote s direction, her hat had fallen off, and she too was shouting furiously.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Alicia took Gryffindor\rquote s penalty, but she was so angry she missed by several feet. The Gryffindor team was losing concentration and the Slytherins, delighted by Malfoy\rquote s foul on Harry, were being spurred on to greater heights.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Slytherin in possession, Slytherin heading for goal \emdash  Montague scores \emdash\rdblquote  Lee groaned. \ldblquote Seventy-twenty to Gryf\-findor. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry was now marking Malfoy so closely their knees kept hit\-ting each other. Harry wasn\rquote t going to let Malfoy anywhere near the Snitch. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Get out of it, Potter!\rdblquote  Malfoy yelled in frustration as he tried to turn and found Harry blocking him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Angelina Johnson gets the Quaffle for Gryffindor, come on, Angelina, COME ON!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry looked around. Every single Slytherin player apart from Malfoy was streaking up the pitch toward Angelina, including the Slytherin Keeper \emdash  they were all going to block her \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry wheeled the Firebolt around, bent so low he was lying flat along the handle, and kicked it forward. Like a bullet, he shot toward the Slytherins.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote AAAAAAARRRGH!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They scattered as the Firebolt zoomed toward them; Angelina\rquote s way was clear.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote SHE SCORES! SHE SCORES! Gryffindor leads by eighty points to twenty!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry, who had almost pelted headlong into the stands, skidded\lang3081  \lang1033 to a halt in midair, reversed, and zoomed back into the middle of the field.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And then he saw something to make his heart stand still. Malfoy was diving, a look of triumph on his face \emdash  there, a few feet above the grass below, was a tiny, golden glimmer \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry urged the Firebolt downward, but Malfoy was miles ahead \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Go! Go! Go!\rdblquote  Harry urged his broom. He was gaining on Mal\-foy \emdash  Harry flattened himself to the broom handle as Bole sent a Bludger at him \emdash  he was at Malfoy\rquote s ankles \emdash  he was level \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry threw himself forward, took both hands off his broom. He knocked Malfoy\rquote s arm out of the way and \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote YES!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He pulled out of his dive, his hand in the air, and the stadium exploded. Harry soared above the crowd, an odd ringing in his ears. The tiny golden ball was held tight in his fist, beating its wings hopelessly against his fingers.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Then Wood was speeding toward him, half-blinded by tears; he seized Harry around the neck and sobbed unrestrainedly into his shoulder. Harry felt two large thumps as Fred and George hit them; then Angelina\rquote s, Alicia\rquote s, and Katie\rquote s voices, \ldblquote\i We\rquote ve won the Cup\i0 ! \i We\rquote ve won the Cup\i0 !\rdblquote  Tangled together in a many-armed hug, the Gryffindor team sank, yelling hoarsely, back to earth.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Wave upon wave of crimson supporters was pouring over the barriers onto the field. Hands were raining down on their backs. Harry had a confused impression of noise and bodies pressing in on him. Then he, and the rest of the team, were hoisted onto the shoulders of the crowd. Thrust into the light, he saw Hagrid, plastered with crimson rosettes \emdash  \ldblquote Yeh beat \rquote em, Harry, yeh beat \rquote em! Wait till I tell Buckbeak!\rdblquote  There was Percy, jumping up and down like a maniac, all dignity forgotten. Professor McGonagall was sob\-bing harder even than Wood, wiping her eyes with an enormous Gryffindor flag; and there, fighting their way toward Harry, were Ron and Hermione. Words failed them. They simply beamed as Harry was borne toward the stands, where Dumbledore stood waiting with the enormous Quidditch Cup.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 If only there had been a dementor around. \'85 As a sobbing Wood passed Harry the Cup, as he lifted it into the air, Harry felt he could have produced the world\rquote s best Patronus.\lang3081\par
