\lang1033\ldblquote Crookshanks!\rdblquote  Hermione moaned. \ldblquote No, go away, Crook\-shanks! Go away!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But the cat was getting nearer \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Scabbers \emdash  NO!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Too late \emdash  the rat had slipped between Ron\rquote s clutching fingers, hit the ground, and scampered away. In one bound, Crookshanks sprang after him, and before Harry or Hermione could stop him, Ron had thrown the Invisibility Cloak off himself and pelted away into the darkness.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Ron\i0 !\rdblquote  Hermione moaned.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She and Harry looked at each other, then followed at a sprint; it was impossible to run full out under the cloak; they pulled it off\lang3081  \lang1033 and it streamed behind them like a banner as they hurtled after Ron; they could hear his feet thundering along ahead and his shouts at Crookshanks.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Get away from him \emdash  get away \emdash  Scabbers, come \i here\i0  \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a loud thud.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Gotcha\i0 ! Get off, you stinking cat \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry and Hermione almost fell over Ron; they skidded to a stop right in front of him. He was sprawled on the ground, but Scabbers was back in his pocket; he had both hands held tight over the quivering lump.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ron \emdash  come on \emdash  back under the cloak \emdash\rdblquote  Hermione panted. \ldblquote Dumbledore \emdash  the Minister \emdash  they\rquote ll be coming back out in a minute \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But before they could cover themselves again, before they could even catch their breath, they heard the soft pounding of gigantic paws. \'85 Something was bounding toward them, quiet as a shadow \emdash  an enormous, pale-eyed, jet-black dog.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry reached for his wand, but too late \emdash  the dog had made an enormous leap and the front paws hit him on the chest; he keeled over backward in a whirl of hair; he felt its hot breath, saw inch-long teeth \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But the force of its leap had carried it too far; it rolled off him. Dazed, feeling as though his ribs were broken, Harry tried to stand up; he could hear it growling as it skidded around for a new attack.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron was on his feet. As the dog sprang back toward them he pushed Harry aside; the dog\rquote s jaws fastened instead around Ron\rquote s outstretched arm. Harry lunged forward, he seized a handful of the brute\rquote s hair, but it was dragging Ron away as easily as though he were a rag doll \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Then, out of nowhere, something hit Harry so hard across the face he was knocked off his feet again. He heard Hermione shriek with pain and fall too.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry groped for his wand, blinking blood out of his eyes \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Lumos\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 he whispered.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The wandlight showed him the trunk of a thick tree; they had chased Scabbers into the shadow of the Whomping Willow and its branches were creaking as though in a high wind, whipping back\-ward and forward to stop them going nearer.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And there, at the base of the trunk, was the dog, dragging Ron backward into a large gap in the roots \emdash  Ron was fighting furi\-ously, but his head and torso were slipping out of sight \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ron!\rdblquote  Harry shouted, trying to follow, but a heavy branch whipped lethally through the air and he was forced backward again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 All they could see now was one of Ron\rquote s legs, which he had hooked around a root in an effort to stop the dog from pulling him farther underground \emdash  but a horrible crack cut the air like a gun\-shot; Ron\rquote s leg had broken, and a moment later, his foot vanished from sight.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry \emdash  we\rquote ve got to go for help \emdash\rdblquote  Hermione gasped; she was bleeding too; the Willow had cut her across the shoulder.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No! That thing\rquote s big enough to eat him; we haven\rquote t got time \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry \emdash  we\rquote re never going to get through without help \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Another branch whipped down at them, twigs clenched like knuckles.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote If that dog can get in, we can,\rdblquote  Harry panted, darting here and there, trying to find a way through the vicious, swishing branches,\lang3081  \lang1033 but he couldn\rquote t get an inch nearer to the tree roots without being in range of the tree\rquote s blows.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, help, help,\rdblquote  Hermione whispered frantically, dancing un\-certainly on the spot, \ldblquote please \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Crookshanks darted forward. He slithered between the battering branches like a snake and placed his front paws upon a knot on the trunk.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Abruptly, as though the tree had been turned to marble, it stopped moving. Not a leaf twitched or shook.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Crookshanks!\rdblquote  Hermione whispered uncertainly. She now grasped Harry\rquote s arm painfully hard. \ldblquote How did he know \emdash  ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He\rquote s friends with that dog,\rdblquote  said Harry grimly. \ldblquote I\rquote ve seen them together. Come on \emdash  and keep your wand out \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They covered the distance to the trunk in seconds, but before they had reached the gap in the roots, Crookshanks had slid into it with a flick of his bottlebrush tail. Harry went next; he crawled for\-ward, headfirst, and slid down an earthy slope to the bottom of a very low tunnel. Crookshanks was a little way along, his eyes flash\-ing in the light from Harry\rquote s wand. Seconds later, Hermione slith\-ered down beside him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Where\rquote s Ron?\rdblquote  she whispered in a terrified voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote This way,\rdblquote  said Harry, setting off, bent-backed, after Crook\-shanks.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Where does this tunnel come out?\rdblquote  Hermione asked breath\-lessly from behind him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I don\rquote t know. \'85 It\rquote s marked on the Marauder\rquote s Map but Fred and George said no one\rquote s ever gotten into it. \'85 It goes off the edge of the map, but it looked like it was heading for Hogsmeade. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They moved as fast as they could, bent almost double; ahead of them, Crookshanks\rquote s tail bobbed in and out of view. On and on went the passage; it felt at least as long as the one to Honey\-dukes. \'85 All Harry could think of was Ron and what the enor\-mous dog might be doing to him. \'85 He was drawing breath in sharp, painful gasps, running at a crouch. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And then the tunnel began to rise; moments later it twisted, and Crookshanks had gone. Instead, Harry could see a patch of dim light through a small opening.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He and Hermione paused, gasping for breath, edging forward. Both raised their wands to see what lay beyond.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It was a room, a very disordered, dusty room. Paper was peeling from the walls; there were stains all over the floor; every piece of furniture was broken as though somebody had smashed it. The windows were all boarded up.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry glanced at Hermione, who looked very frightened but nodded.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry pulled himself out of the hole, staring around. The room was deserted, but a door to their right stood open, leading to a shadowy hallway. Hermione suddenly grabbed Harry\rquote s arm again. Her wide eyes were traveling around the boarded windows.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry,\rdblquote  she whispered, \ldblquote I think we\rquote re in the Shrieking Shack.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry looked around. His eyes fell on a wooden chair near them. Large chunks had been torn out of it; one of the legs had been ripped off entirely.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ghosts didn\rquote t do that,\rdblquote  he said slowly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 At that moment, there was a creak overhead. Something had moved upstairs. Both of them looked up at the ceiling. Hermione\rquote s\lang3081  \lang1033 grip on Harry\rquote s arm was so tight he was losing feeling in his fingers. He raised his eyebrows at her; she nodded again and let go.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Quietly as they could, they crept out into the hall and up the crumbling staircase. Everything was covered in a thick layer of dust except the floor, where a wide shiny stripe had been made by some\-thing being dragged upstairs.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They reached the dark landing.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Nox,\i0\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 they whispered together, and the lights at the end of their wands went out. Only one door was open. As they crept toward it, they heard movement from behind it; a low moan, and then a deep, loud purring. They exchanged a last look, a last nod.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Wand held tightly before him, Harry kicked the door wide open.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 On a magnificent four-poster bed with dusty hangings lay Crookshanks, purring loudly at the sight of them. On the floor be\-side him, clutching his leg, which stuck out at a strange angle, was Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry and Hermione dashed across to him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ron \emdash  are you okay?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Where\rquote s the dog?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Not a dog,\rdblquote  Ron moaned. His teeth were gritted with pain. \ldblquote Harry, it\rquote s a trap \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i He\rquote s the dog\lang3081\i0  \lang1033\'85 \i he\rquote s an Animagus. \'85\i0\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron was staring over Harry\rquote s shoulder. Harry wheeled around. With a snap, the man in the shadows closed the door behind them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A mass of filthy, matted hair hung to his elbows. If eyes hadn\rquote t been shining out of the deep, dark sockets, he might have been a\lang3081  \lang1033 corpse. The waxy skin was stretched so tightly over the bones of his face, it looked like a skull. His yellow teeth were bared in a grin. It was Sirius Black.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Expelliarmus\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 he croaked, pointing Ron\rquote s wand at them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry\rquote s and Hermione\rquote s wands shot out of their hands, high in the air, and Black caught them. Then he took a step closer. His eyes were fixed on Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I thought you\rquote d come and help your friend,\rdblquote  he said hoarsely. His voice sounded as though he had long since lost the habit of us\-ing it. \ldblquote Your father would have done the same for me. Brave of you, not to run for a teacher. I\rquote m grateful \'85 it will make everything much easier. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The taunt about his father rang in Harry\rquote s ears as though Black had bellowed it. A boiling hate erupted in Harry\rquote s chest, leaving no place for fear. For the first time in his life, he wanted his wand back in his hand, not to defend himself, but to attack \'85 to kill. With\-out knowing what he was doing, he started forward, but there was a sudden movement on either side of him and two pairs of hands grabbed him and held him back. \'85 \ldblquote No, Harry!\rdblquote  Hermione gasped in a petrified whisper; Ron, however, spoke to Black.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote If you want to kill Harry, you\rquote ll have to kill us too!\rdblquote  he said fiercely, though the effort of standing upright was draining him of still more color, and he swayed slightly as he spoke.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Something flickered in Black\rquote s shadowed eyes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Lie down,\rdblquote  he said quietly to Ron. \ldblquote You will damage that leg even more.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Did you hear me?\rdblquote  Ron said weakly, though he was clinging painfully to Harry to stay upright. \ldblquote You\rquote ll have to kill all three of us!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There\rquote ll be only one murder here tonight,\rdblquote  said Black, and his grin widened.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Why\rquote s that?\rdblquote  Harry spat, trying to wrench himself free of Ron and Hermione. \ldblquote Didn\rquote t care last time, did you? Didn\rquote t mind slaughtering all those Muggles to get at Pettigrew. \'85 What\rquote s the matter, gone soft in Azkaban?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry!\rdblquote  Hermione whimpered. \ldblquote Be quiet!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote HE KILLED MY MUM AND DAD!\rdblquote  Harry roared, and with a huge effort he broke free of Hermione\rquote s and Ron\rquote s restraint and lunged forward \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He had forgotten about magic \emdash  he had forgotten that he was short and skinny and thirteen, whereas Black was a tall, full-grown man \emdash  all Harry knew was that he wanted to hurt Black as badly as he could and that he didn\rquote t care how much he got hurt in re\-turn \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Perhaps it was the shock of Harry doing something so stupid, but Black didn\rquote t raise the wands in time \emdash  one of Harry\rquote s hands fastened over his wasted wrist, forcing the wand tips away; the knuckles of Harry\rquote s other hand collided with the side of Black\rquote s head and they fell, backward, into the wall \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione was screaming; Ron was yelling; there was a blinding flash as the wands in Black\rquote s hand sent a jet of sparks into the air that missed Harry\rquote s face by inches; Harry felt the shrunken arm under his fingers twisting madly, but he clung on, his other hand punching every part of Black it could find.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But Black\rquote s free hand had found Harry\rquote s throat \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No,\rdblquote  he hissed, \ldblquote I\rquote ve waited too long \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The fingers tightened, Harry choked, his glasses askew.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Then he saw Hermione\rquote s foot swing out of nowhere. Black let go of Harry with a grunt of pain; Ron had thrown himself on Black\rquote s wand hand and Harry heard a faint clatter \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He fought free of the tangle of bodies and saw his own wand rolling across the floor; he threw himself toward it but \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Argh!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Crookshanks had joined the fray; both sets of front claws had sunk themselves deep into Harry\rquote s arm; Harry threw him off, but Crookshanks now darted toward Harry\rquote s wand \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote NO YOU DON\rquote T!\rdblquote  roared Harry, and he aimed a kick at Crookshanks that made the cat leap aside, spitting; Harry snatched up his wand and turned \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Get out of the way!\rdblquote  he shouted at Ron and Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They didn\rquote t need telling twice. Hermione, gasping for breath, her lip bleeding, scrambled aside, snatching up her and Ron\rquote s wands. Ron crawled to the four-poster and collapsed onto it, pant\-ing, his white face now tinged with green, both hands clutching his broken leg.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Black was sprawled at the bottom of the wall. His thin chest rose and fell rapidly as he watched Harry walking slowly nearer, his wand pointing straight at Black\rquote s heart.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Going to kill me, Harry?\rdblquote  he whispered.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry stopped right above him, his wand still pointing at Black\rquote s chest, looking down at him. A livid bruise was rising around Black\rquote s left eye and his nose was bleeding.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You killed my parents,\rdblquote  said Harry, his voice shaking slightly, but his wand hand quite steady.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Black stared up at him out of those sunken eyes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I don\rquote t deny it,\rdblquote  he said very quietly. \ldblquote But if you knew the whole story.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The whole story?\rdblquote  Harry repeated, a furious pounding in his ears. \ldblquote You sold them to Voldemort. That\rquote s all I need to know.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote ve got to listen to me,\rdblquote  Black said, and there was a note of urgency in his voice now. \ldblquote You\rquote ll regret it if you don\rquote t. \'85 You don\rquote t understand. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I understand a lot better than you think,\rdblquote  said Harry, and his voice shook more than ever. \ldblquote You never heard her, did you? My mum \'85 trying to stop Voldemort killing me \'85 and you did that \'85 you did it. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Before either of them could say another word, something ginger streaked past Harry; Crookshanks leapt onto Black\rquote s chest and set\-tled himself there, right over Black\rquote s heart. Black blinked and looked down at the cat.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Get off,\rdblquote  he murmured, trying to push Crookshanks off him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But Crookshanks sank his claws into Black\rquote s robes and wouldn\rquote t shift. He turned his ugly, squashed face to Harry and looked up at him with those great yellow eyes. To his right, Hermione gave a dry sob.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry stared down at Black and Crookshanks, his grip tighten\-ing on the wand. So what if he had to kill the cat too? It was in league with Black. \'85 If it was prepared to die, trying to protect Black, that wasn\rquote t Harry\rquote s business. \'85 If Black wanted to save it, that only proved he cared more for Crookshanks than for Harry\rquote s parents. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry raised the wand. Now was the moment to do it. Now was the moment to avenge his mother and father. He was going to kill Black. He had to kill Black. This was his chance. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The seconds lengthened. And still Harry stood frozen there, wand poised, Black staring up at him, Crookshanks on his chest. Ron\rquote s ragged breathing came from near the bed; Hermione was quite silent.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And then came a new sound \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Muffled footsteps were echoing up through the floor \emdash  some\-one was moving downstairs.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote WE\rquote RE UP HERE!\rdblquote  Hermione screamed suddenly. \ldblquote WE\rquote RE UP HERE \emdash  SIRIUS BLACK \emdash  \i QUICK\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Black made a startled movement that almost dislodged Crook\-shanks; Harry gripped his wand convulsively \emdash  \i Do it now\i0 ! said a voice in his head \emdash  but the footsteps were thundering up the stairs and Harry still hadn\rquote t done it.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The door of the room burst open in a shower of red sparks and Harry wheeled around as Professor Lupin came hurtling into the room, his face bloodless, his wand raised and ready. His eyes flick\-ered over Ron, lying on the floor, over Hermione, cowering next to the door, to Harry, standing there with his wand covering Black, and then to Black himself, crumpled and bleeding at Harry\rquote s feet.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Expelliarmus\i0 !\rdblquote  Lupin shouted.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry\rquote s wand flew once more out of his hand; so did the two Hermione was holding. Lupin caught them all deftly, then moved into the room, staring at Black, who still had Crookshanks lying protectively across his chest.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry stood there, feeling suddenly empty. He hadn\rquote t done it. His nerve had failed him. Black was going to be handed back to the dementors.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Then Lupin spoke, in a very tense voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Where is he, Sirius?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry looked quickly at Lupin. He didn\rquote t understand what Lupin meant. Who was Lupin talking about? He turned to look at Black again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Black\rquote s face was quite expressionless. For a few seconds, he didn\rquote t move at all. Then, very slowly, he raised his empty hand and pointed straight at Ron. Mystified, Harry glanced around at Ron, who looked bewildered.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But then \'85 ,\rdblquote  Lupin muttered, staring at Black so intently it seemed he was trying to read his mind, \ldblquote\'85 why hasn\rquote t he shown himself before now? Unless\rdblquote  \emdash  Lupin\rquote s eyes suddenly widened, as though he was seeing something beyond Black, something none of the rest could see, \ldblquote\emdash  unless \i he\i0  was the one \'85 unless you switched \'85 without telling me?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Very slowly, his sunken gaze never leaving Lupin\rquote s face, Black nodded.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Professor,\rdblquote  Harry interrupted loudly, \ldblquote what\rquote s going on \emdash  ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But he never finished the question, because what he saw made his voice die in his throat. Lupin was lowering his wand, gazing fixedly at Black. The Professor walked to Black\rquote s side, seized his hand, pulled him to his feet so that Crookshanks fell to the floor, and embraced Black like a brother.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry felt as though the bottom had dropped out of his stomach.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I DON\rquote T BELIEVE IT!\rdblquote  Hermione screamed.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Lupin let go of Black and turned to her. She had raised herself off the floor and was pointing at Lupin, wild-eyed. \ldblquote You \emdash  you \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hermione \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote  \emdash  you and him!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hermione, calm down \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I didn\rquote t tell anyone!\rdblquote  Hermione shrieked. \ldblquote I\rquote ve been covering up for you \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hermione, listen to me, please!\rdblquote  Lupin shouted. \ldblquote I can ex\-plain \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry could feel himself shaking, not with fear, but with a fresh wave of fury.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I trusted you,\rdblquote  he shouted at Lupin, his voice wavering out of control, \ldblquote and all the time you\rquote ve been his friend!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote re wrong,\rdblquote  said Lupin. \ldblquote I haven\rquote t been Sirius\rquote s friend, but I am now \emdash  Let me explain. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote NO!\rdblquote  Hermione screamed. \ldblquote Harry, don\rquote t trust him, he\rquote s been helping Black get into the castle, he wants you dead too \emdash  \i he\rquote s a werewolf\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a ringing silence. Everyone\rquote s eyes were now on Lupin, who looked remarkably calm, though rather pale.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Not at all up to your usual standard, Hermione,\rdblquote  he said. \ldblquote Only one out of three, I\rquote m afraid. I have not been helping Sirius get into the castle and I certainly don\rquote t want Harry dead. \'85\rdblquote  An odd shiver passed over his face. \ldblquote But I won\rquote t deny that I am a were\-wolf.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron made a valiant effort to get up again but fell back with a whimper of pain. Lupin made toward him, looking concerned, but Ron gasped,\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Get away from me, werewolf\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Lupin stopped dead. Then, with an obvious effort, he turned to Hermione and said, \ldblquote How long have you known?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033  \ldblquote Ages,\rdblquote  Hermione whispered. \ldblquote Since I did Professor Snape\rquote s es\-say. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He\rquote ll be delighted,\rdblquote  said Lupin coolly. \ldblquote He assigned that essay hoping someone would realize what my symptoms meant. \'85 Did you check the lunar chart and realize that I was always ill at the full moon? Or did you realize that the boggart changed into the moon when it saw me?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Both,\rdblquote  Hermione said quietly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Lupin forced a laugh.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote re the cleverest witch of your age I\rquote ve ever met, Hermione.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m not,\rdblquote  Hermione whispered. \ldblquote If I\rquote d been a bit cleverer, I\rquote d have told everyone what you are!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But they already know,\rdblquote  said Lupin. \ldblquote At least, the staff do.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Dumbledore hired you when he knew you were a werewolf?\rdblquote  Ron gasped. \ldblquote Is he mad?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Some of the staff thought so,\rdblquote  said Lupin. \ldblquote He had to work very hard to convince certain teachers that I\rquote m trustworthy \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote AND HE WAS WRONG!\rdblquote  Harry yelled. \ldblquote YOU\rquote VE BEEN HELPING HIM ALL THE TIME!\rdblquote  He was pointing at Black, who suddenly crossed to the four-poster bed and sank onto it, his face hidden in one shaking hand. Crookshanks leapt up beside him and stepped onto his lap, purring. Ron edged away from both of them, dragging his leg.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I have \i not\i0  been helping Sirius,\rdblquote  said Lupin. \ldblquote If you\rquote ll give me a chance, I\rquote ll explain. Look \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He separated Harry\rquote s, Ron\rquote s and Hermione\rquote s wands and threw each back to its owner; Harry caught his, stunned.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There,\rdblquote  said Lupin, sticking his own wand back into his belt. \ldblquote You\rquote re armed, we\rquote re not. Now will you listen?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry didn\rquote t know what to think. Was it a trick?\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote If you haven\rquote t been helping him,\rdblquote  he said, with a furious glance at Black, \ldblquote how did you know he was here?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The map,\rdblquote  said Lupin. \ldblquote The Marauder\rquote s Map. I was in my of\-fice examining it \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You know how to work it?\rdblquote  Harry said suspiciously.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Of course I know how to work it,\rdblquote  said Lupin, waving his hand impatiently. \ldblquote I helped write it. I\rquote m Moony \emdash  that was my friends\rquote  nickname for me at school.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You \i wrote\lang3081\i0  \lang1033\emdash  ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The important thing is, I was watching it carefully this evening, because I had an idea that you, Ron, and Hermione might try and sneak out of the castle to visit Hagrid before his hippogriff was ex\-ecuted. And I was right, wasn\rquote t I?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He had started to pace up and down, looking at them. Little patches of dust rose at his feet.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You might have been wearing your father\rquote s old cloak, Harry \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How d\rquote you know about the cloak?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The number of times I saw James disappearing under it\'85 ,\rdblquote  said Lupin, waving an impatient hand again. \ldblquote The point is, even if you\rquote re wearing an Invisibility Cloak, you still show up on the Marauder\rquote s Map. I watched you cross the grounds and enter Hagrid\rquote s hut. Twenty minutes later, you left Hagrid, and set off back toward the castle. But you were now accompanied by some\-body else.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What?\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote No, we weren\rquote t!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I couldn\rquote t believe my eyes,\rdblquote  said Lupin, still pacing, and ignor\-ing Harry\rquote s interruption. \ldblquote I thought the map must be malfunc\-tioning. How could he be with you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No one was with us!\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And then I saw another dot, moving fast toward you, labeled\lang3081  \lang1033\i Sirius Black. \'85\i0  I saw him collide with you; I watched as he pulled\lang3081  \lang1033 two of you into the Whomping Willow \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote One of us!\rdblquote  Ron said angrily.\par
\ldblquote No, Ron,\rdblquote  said Lupin. \ldblquote Two of you.\rdblquote\par
He had stopped his pacing, his eyes moving over Ron.\par
\ldblquote Do you think I could have a look at the rat?\rdblquote  he said evenly.\par
\ldblquote What?\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote What\rquote s Scabbers got to do with it?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote Everything,\rdblquote  said Lupin. \ldblquote Could I see him, please?\rdblquote\par
Ron hesitated, then put a hand inside his robes. Scabbers\lang3081  \lang1033 emerged, thrashing desperately; Ron had to seize his long bald tail\lang3081  \lang1033 to stop him escaping. Crookshanks stood up on Black\rquote s leg and\lang3081  \lang1033 made a soft hissing noise.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Lupin moved closer to Ron. He seemed to be holding his breath\lang3081  \lang1033 as he gazed intently at Scabbers.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What?\rdblquote  Ron said again, holding Scabbers close to him, looking\lang3081  \lang1033 scared. \ldblquote What\rquote s my rat got to do with anything?\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote That\rquote s not a rat,\rdblquote  croaked Sirius Black suddenly.\par
\ldblquote What d\rquote you mean \emdash  of course he\rquote s a rat \emdash\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote No, he\rquote s not,\rdblquote  said Lupin quietly. \ldblquote He\rquote s a wizard.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote An Animagus,\rdblquote  said Black, \ldblquote by the name of Peter Pettigrew.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\par
