Hermione screamed. Black leapt to his feet. Harry felt as though he\rquote d received a huge electric shock.\par
\ldblquote I found this at the base of the Whomping Willow,\rdblquote  said Snape, throwing the cloak aside, careful to keep this wand pointing di\-rectly at Lupin\rquote s chest. \ldblquote Very useful, Potter, I thank you. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Snape was slightly breathless, but his face was full of suppressed triumph. \ldblquote You\rquote re wondering, perhaps, how I knew you were here?\rdblquote  he said, his eyes glittering. \ldblquote I\rquote ve just been to your office, Lupin. You forgot to take your potion tonight, so I took a gobletful along. And very lucky I did \'85 lucky for me, I mean. Lying on your desk was a certain map. One glance at it told me all I needed to know. I saw you running along this passageway and out of sight.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Severus \emdash\rdblquote  Lupin began, but Snape overrode him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote ve told the headmaster again and again that you\rquote re helping your old friend Black into the castle, Lupin, and here\rquote s the proof.\lang3081  \lang1033 Not even I dreamed you would have the nerve to use this old place as your hideout \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Severus, you\rquote re making a mistake,\rdblquote  said Lupin urgently. \ldblquote You haven\rquote t heard everything \emdash  I can explain \emdash  Sirius is not here to kill Harry \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Two more for Azkaban tonight,\rdblquote  said Snape, his eyes now gleaming fanatically. \ldblquote I shall be interested to see how Dumbledore takes this. \'85 He was quite convinced you were harmless, you know, Lupin \'85 a \i tame\i0  werewolf\lang3081  \lang1033\emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You fool,\rdblquote  said Lupin softly. \ldblquote Is a schoolboy grudge worth putting an innocent man back inside Azkaban?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 BANG! Thin, snakelike cords burst from the end of Snape\rquote s wand and twisted themselves around Lupin\rquote s mouth, wrists, and ankles; he overbalanced and fell to the floor, unable to move. With a roar of rage, Black started toward Snape, but Snape pointed his wand straight between Black\rquote s eyes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Give me a reason,\rdblquote  he whispered. \ldblquote Give me a reason to do it, and I swear I will.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Black stopped dead. It would have been impossible to say which face showed more hatred.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry stood there, paralyzed, not knowing what to do or whom to believe. He glanced around at Ron and Hermione. Ron looked just as confused as he did, still fighting to keep hold on the strug\-gling Scabbers. Hermione, however, took an uncertain step toward Snape and said, in a very breathless voice, \ldblquote Professor Snape \emdash  it \emdash  it wouldn\rquote t hurt to hear what they\rquote ve got to say, w \emdash  would it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Miss Granger, you are already facing suspension from this school,\rdblquote  Snape spat. \ldblquote You, Potter, and Weasley are out-of-bounds,\lang3081  \lang1033 in the company of a convicted murderer and a werewolf. For once in your life, \i hold your tongue.\i0\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But if\lang3081  \lang1033\emdash  if there was a mistake \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote KEEP QUIET, YOU STUPID GIRL!\rdblquote  Snape shouted, looking suddenly quite deranged. \ldblquote DON\rquote T TALK ABOUT WHAT YOU DON\rquote T UNDERSTAND!\rdblquote  A few sparks shot out of the end of his wand, which was still pointed at Black\rquote s face. Hermione fell silent.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Vengeance is very sweet,\rdblquote  Snape breathed at Black. \ldblquote How I hoped I would be the one to catch you. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The joke\rquote s on you again, Severus,\rdblquote  Black snarled. \ldblquote As long as this boy brings his rat up to the castle\rdblquote  \emdash  he jerked his head at Ron \emdash  \ldblquote I\rquote ll come quietly. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Up to the castle?\rdblquote  said Snape silkily. \ldblquote I don\rquote t think we need to go that far. All I have to do is call the dementors once we get out of the Willow. They\rquote ll be very pleased to see you, Black \'85 pleased enough to give you a little kiss, I daresay. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 What little color there was in Black\rquote s face left it.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You \emdash  you\rquote ve got to hear me out,\rdblquote  he croaked. \ldblquote The rat \emdash  look at the rat \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But there was a mad glint in Snape\rquote s eyes that Harry had never seen before. He seemed beyond reason.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Come on, all of you,\rdblquote  he said. He clicked his fingers, and the ends of the cords that bound Lupin flew to his hands. \ldblquote I\rquote ll drag the werewolf. Perhaps the dementors will have a kiss for him too \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
