\lang1033\ldblquote I don\rquote t know how I did it,\rdblquote  he said slowly. \ldblquote I think the only rea\-son I never lost my mind is that I knew I was innocent. That wasn\rquote t a happy thought, so the dementors couldn\rquote t suck it out of me \'85 but it kept me sane and knowing who I am \'85 helped me keep my powers \'85 so when it all became \'85 too much \'85 I could trans\-form in my cell\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 become a dog. Dementors can\rquote t see, you know. \'85\rdblquote  He swallowed. \ldblquote They feel their way toward people by feeding off their emotions. \'85 They could tell that my feelings were less \emdash  less human, less complex when I was a dog \'85 but they thought, of course, that I was losing my mind like everyone else in there, so it didn\rquote t trouble them. But I was weak, very weak, and I had no hope of driving them away from me without a wand. \'85\lang3081\par
