Harry had never been part of a stranger group. Crook\-shanks led the way down the stairs; Lupin, Pettigrew, and Ron went next, looking like entrants in a six-legged race. Next came Professor Snape, drifting creepily along, his toes hitting each stair as they descended, held up by his own wand, which was being pointed at him by Sirius. Harry and Hermione brought up the rear.\par
Getting back into the tunnel was difficult. Lupin, Pettigrew, and Ron had to turn sideways to manage it; Lupin still had Pettigrew covered with his wand. Harry could see them edging awkwardly along the tunnel in single file. Crookshanks was still in the lead. Harry went right after Black, who was still making Snape drift along ahead of them; he kept bumping his lolling head on the low ceiling. Harry had the impression Black was making no effort to prevent this.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You know what this means?\rdblquote  Black said abruptly to Harry as they made their slow progress along the tunnel. \ldblquote Turning Pettigrew in?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote re free,\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes \'85 ,\rdblquote  said Black. \ldblquote But I\rquote m also \emdash  I don\rquote t know if anyone ever told you \emdash  I\rquote m your godfather.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, I knew that,\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 your parents appointed me your guardian,\rdblquote  said Black stiffly. \ldblquote If anything happened to them \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry waited. Did Black mean what he thought he meant?\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote ll understand, of course, if you want to stay with your aunt and uncle,\rdblquote  said Black. \ldblquote But\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 well \'85 think about it. Once my name\rquote s cleared \'85 if you wanted a \'85 a different home \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Some sort of explosion took place in the pit of Harry\rquote s stomach.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What \emdash  live with you?\rdblquote  he said, accidentally cracking his head on a bit of rock protruding from the ceiling. \ldblquote Leave the Dursleys?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Of course, I thought you wouldn\rquote t want to,\rdblquote  said Black quickly. \ldblquote I understand, I just thought I\rquote d \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Are you insane?\rdblquote  said Harry, his voice easily as croaky as Black\rquote s. \ldblquote Of course I want to leave the Dursleys! Have you got a house? When can I move in?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Black turned right around to look at him; Snape\rquote s head was scraping the ceiling but Black didn\rquote t seem to care.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You want to?\rdblquote  he said. \ldblquote You mean it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, I mean it!\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Black\rquote s gaunt face broke into the first true smile Harry had seen upon it. The difference it made was startling, as though a person ten years younger were shining through the starved mask; for a mo\-ment, he was recognizable as the man who had laughed at Harry\rquote s parents\rquote  wedding.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They did not speak again until they had reached the end of the tunnel. Crookshanks darted up first; he had evidently pressed his\lang3081  \lang1033 paw to the knot on the trunk, because Lupin, Pettigrew, and Ron clambered upward without any sound of savaging branches.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Black saw Snape up through the hole, then stood back for Harry and Hermione to pass. At last, all of them were out.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The grounds were very dark now; the only light came from the distant windows of the castle. Without a word, they set off. Petti\-grew was still wheezing and occasionally whimpering. Harry\rquote s mind was buzzing. He was going to leave the Dursleys. He was go\-ing to live with Sirius Black, his parents\rquote  best friend. \'85 He felt dazed. \'85 What would happen when he told the Dursleys he was going to live with the convict they\rquote d seen on television\'85 !\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote One wrong move, Peter,\rdblquote  said Lupin threateningly ahead. His wand was still pointed sideways at Pettigrew\rquote s chest.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Silently they tramped through the grounds, the castle lights growing slowly larger. Snape was still drifting weirdly ahead of Black, his chin bumping on his chest. And then \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A cloud shifted. There were suddenly dim shadows on the ground. Their party was bathed in moonlight.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Snape collided with Lupin, Pettigrew, and Ron, who had stopped abruptly. Black froze. He flung out one arm to make Harry and Hermione stop.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry could see Lupin\rquote s silhouette. He had gone rigid. Then his limbs began to shake.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, my \emdash\rdblquote  Hermione gasped. \ldblquote He didn\rquote t take his potion tonight! He\rquote s not safe!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Run,\rdblquote  Black whispered. \ldblquote Run. Now.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But Harry couldn\rquote t run. Ron was chained to Pettigrew and Lupin. He leapt forward but Black caught him around the chest and threw him back.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Leave it to me \emdash  RUN!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a terrible snarling noise. Lupin\rquote s head was lengthening. So was his body. His shoulders were hunching. Hair was sprouting visibly on his face and hands, which were curling into clawed paws. Crookshanks\rquote s hair was on end again; he was backing away \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 As the werewolf reared, snapping its long jaws, Sirius disap\-peared from Harry\rquote s side. He had transformed. The enormous, bearlike dog bounded forward. As the werewolf wrenched itself free of the manacle binding it, the dog seized it about the neck and pulled it backward, away from Ron and Pettigrew. They were locked, jaw to jaw, claws ripping at each other \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry stood, transfixed by the sight, too intent upon the battle to notice anything else. It was Hermione\rquote s scream that alerted him \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Pettigrew had dived for Lupin\rquote s dropped wand. Ron, unsteady on his bandaged leg, fell. There was a bang, a burst of light \emdash  and Ron lay motionless on the ground. Another bang \emdash  Crookshanks flew into the air and back to the earth in a heap.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Expelliarmus\i0 !\rdblquote  Harry yelled, pointing his own wand at Petti\-grew; Lupin\rquote s wand flew high into the air and out of sight. \ldblquote Stay where you are!\rdblquote  Harry shouted, running forward.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Too late. Pettigrew had transformed. Harry saw his bald tail whip through the manacle on Ron\rquote s outstretched arm and heard a scurrying through the grass.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a howl and a rumbling growl; Harry turned to see the werewolf taking flight; it was galloping into the forest \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Sirius, he\rquote s gone, Pettigrew transformed!\rdblquote  Harry yelled.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Black was bleeding; there were gashes across his muzzle and back, but at Harry\rquote s words he scrambled up again, and in an\lang3081  \lang1033 instant, the sound of his paws faded to silence as he pounded away across the grounds.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry and Hermione dashed over to Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What did he do to him?\rdblquote  Hermione whispered. Ron\rquote s eyes were only half-closed, his mouth hung open; he was definitely alive, they could hear him breathing, but he didn\rquote t seem to recognize them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I don\rquote t know. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry looked desperately around. Black and Lupin both gone \'85 they had no one but Snape for company, still hanging, unconscious, in midair.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We\rquote d better get them up to the castle and tell someone,\rdblquote  said Harry, pushing his hair out of his eyes, trying to think straight. Come \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But then, from beyond the range of their vision, they heard a yelping, a whining: a dog in pain. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Sirius,\rdblquote  Harry muttered, staring into the darkness.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He had a moment\rquote s indecision, but there was nothing they could do for Ron at the moment, and by the sound of it, Black was in trouble \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry set off at a run, Hermione right behind him. The yelping seemed to be coming from the ground near the edge of the lake. They pelted toward it, and Harry, running flat out, felt the cold without realizing what it must mean \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The yelping stopped abruptly. As they reached the lakeshore, they saw why \emdash  Sirius had turned back into a man. He was crouched on all fours, his hands over his head.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Nooo,\i0\rdblquote  he moaned. \ldblquote\i Noooo\i0  \'85 \i please. \'85\i0\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And then Harry saw them. Dementors, at least a hundred of\lang3081  \lang1033 them, gliding in a black mass around the lake toward them. He spun around, the familiar, icy cold penetrating his insides, fog starting to obscure his vision; more were appearing out of the dark\-ness on every side; they were encircling them. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hermione, think of something happy!\rdblquote  Harry yelled, raising his wand, blinking furiously to try and clear his vision, shaking his head to rid it of the faint screaming that had started inside it \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\i I\rquote m going to live with my godfather. I\rquote m leaving the Dursleys.\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033 He forced himself to think of Black, and only Black, and began to chant: \ldblquote\i Expecto patronum\i0 ! \i Expecto patronum\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Black gave a shudder, rolled over, and lay motionless on the ground, pale as death.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\i He\rquote ll be all right. I\rquote m going to go and live with him.\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Expecto patronum\i0 ! Hermione, help me! \i Expecto patronum\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Expecto\i0  \emdash\rdblquote  Hermione whispered, \ldblquote\i expecto\i0  \emdash  \i expecto\i0  \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But she couldn\rquote t do it. The dementors were closing in, barely ten feet from them. They formed a solid wall around Harry and Hermione, and were getting closer. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i EXPECTO PATRONUM\i0 !\rdblquote  Harry yelled, trying to blot the screaming from his ears. \ldblquote\i EXPECTO PATRONUM\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A thin wisp of silver escaped his wand and hovered like mist be\-fore him. At the same moment, Harry felt Hermione collapse next to him. He was alone \'85 completely alone. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Expecto\i0  \emdash  \i expecto patronum\i0  \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry felt his knees hit the cold grass. Fog was clouding his eyes. With a huge effort, he fought to remember \emdash  Sirius was inno\-cent \emdash  innocent \emdash  \i We\rquote ll be okay\i0  \emdash  \i I\rquote m going to live with him\i0  \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Expecto\lang3081  \lang1033 patronum\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 he gasped.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 By the feeble light of his formless Patronus, he saw a dementor halt, very close to him. It couldn\rquote t walk through the cloud of silver mist Harry had conjured. A dead, slimy hand slid out from under the cloak. It made a gesture as though to sweep the Patronus aside.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No \emdash  \i no\i0  \emdash\rdblquote  Harry gasped. \ldblquote He\rquote s innocent\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 \i expecto\i0  \emdash  \i expecto patronum\i0  \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He could feel them watching him, hear their rattling breath like an evil wind around him. The nearest dementor seemed to be con\-sidering him. Then it raised both its rotting hands \emdash  and lowered its hood.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Where there should have been eyes, there was only thin, gray scabbed skin, stretched blankly over empty sockets. But there was a mouth \'85 a gaping, shapeless hole, sucking the air with the sound of a death rattle.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A paralyzing terror filled Harry so that he couldn\rquote t move or speak. His Patronus flickered and died.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 White fog was blinding him. He had to fight\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 \i expecto pa\-tronum\i0  \'85 he couldn\rquote t see \'85 and in the distance, he heard the fa\-miliar screaming \'85 \i expecto patronum\i0  \'85 he groped in the mist for Sirius, and found his arm \'85 they weren\rquote t going to take him. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But a pair of strong, clammy hands suddenly attached them\-selves around Harry\rquote s neck. They were forcing his face upward. \'85 He could feel its breath. \'85 It was going to get rid of him first. \'85 He could feel its putrid breath. \'85 His mother was screaming in his ears. \'85 She was going to be the last thing he ever heard \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And then, through the fog that was drowning him, he thought he saw a silvery light growing brighter and brighter. \'85 He felt\lang3081  \lang1033 himself fall forward onto the grass. \'85 Facedown, too weak to move, sick and shaking, Harry opened his eyes. The dementor must have released him. The blinding light was illuminating the grass around him. \'85 The screaming had stopped, the cold was ebbing away. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Something was driving the dementors back. \'85 It was circling around him and Black and Hermione. \'85 They were leaving. \'85 The air was warm again. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 With every ounce of strength he could muster, Harry raised his head a few inches and saw an animal amid the light, galloping away across the lake. \'85 Eyes blurred with sweat, Harry tried to make out what it was. \'85 It was as bright as a unicorn. \'85 Fighting to stay conscious, Harry watched it canter to a halt as it reached the opposite shore. For a moment, Harry saw, by its brightness, some\-body welcoming it back \'85 raising his hand to pat it\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 someone who looked strangely familiar \'85 but it couldn\rquote t be \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry didn\rquote t understand. He couldn\rquote t think anymore. He felt the last of his strength leave him, and his head hit the ground as he fainted.\lang3081\par
