\lang1033\ldblquote Black had bewitched them, I saw it immediately. A Confundus Charm, to judge by their behavior. They seemed to think there was a possibility he was innocent. They weren\rquote t responsible for their ac\-tions. On the other hand, their interference might have permitted\lang3081  \lang1033 Black to escape. \'85 They obviously thought they were going to catch Black single-handed. They\rquote ve got away with a great deal be\-fore now. \'85 I\rquote m afraid it\rquote s given them a rather high opinion of themselves \'85 and of course Potter has always been allowed an ex\-traordinary amount of license by the headmaster \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
