\lang1033\ldblquote\i Prongs\i0 ,\rdblquote  he whispered.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But as his trembling fingertips stretched toward the creature, it vanished.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry stood there, hand still outstretched. Then, with a great leap of his heart, he heard hooves behind him \emdash  he whirled around and saw Hermione dashing toward him, dragging Buck\-beak behind her.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i What did you do\i0 ?\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 she said fiercely. \ldblquote You said you were only go\-ing to keep a lookout!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I just saved all our lives \'85 ,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote Get behind here \emdash  behind this bush \emdash  I\rquote ll explain.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione listened to what had just happened with her mouth open yet again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Did anyone see you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes, haven\rquote t you been listening? \i I\i0  saw me but I thought I was my dad! It\rquote s okay!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry, I can\rquote t believe it. \'85 You conjured up a Patronus that drove away all those dementors! That\rquote s very, \i very\i0  advanced magic. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I knew I could do it this time,\rdblquote  said Harry, \ldblquote because I\rquote d already done it. \'85 Does that make sense?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I don\rquote t know \emdash  Harry, look at Snape!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Together they peered around the bush at the other bank. Snape had regained consciousness. He was conjuring stretchers and lift\-ing the limp forms of Harry, Hermione, and Black onto them. A fourth stretcher, no doubt bearing Ron, was already floating at his side. Then, wand held out in front of him, he moved them away toward the castle.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Right, it\rquote s nearly time,\rdblquote  said Hermione tensely, looking at her watch. \ldblquote We\rquote ve got about forty-five minutes until Dumbledore locks the door to the hospital wing. We\rquote ve got to rescue Sirius and get back into the ward before anybody realizes we\rquote re missing. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They waited, watching the moving clouds reflected in the lake, while the bush next to them whispered in the breeze. Buckbeak, bored, was ferreting for worms again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote D\rquote  you reckon he\rquote s up there yet?\rdblquote  said Harry, checking his watch. He looked up at the castle and began counting the windows to the right of the West Tower.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Look!\rdblquote  Hermione whispered. \ldblquote Who\rquote s that? Someone\rquote s coming back out of the castle!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry stared through the darkness. The man was hurrying across the grounds, toward one of the entrances. Something shiny glinted in his belt.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Macnair!\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote The executioner! He\rquote s gone to get the dementors! This is it, Hermione \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione put her hands on Buckbeak\rquote s back and Harry gave her a leg up. Then he placed his foot on one of the lower branches of the bush and climbed up in front of her. He pulled Buckbeak\rquote s rope back over his neck and tied it to the other side of his collar like reins.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ready?\rdblquote  he whispered to Hermione. \ldblquote You\rquote d better hold on to me \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He nudged Buckbeak\rquote s sides with his heels.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Buckbeak soared straight into the dark air. Harry gripped his flanks with his knees, feeling the great wings rising powerfully be\-neath them. Hermione was holding Harry very tight around the\lang3081  \lang1033 waist; he could hear her muttering, \ldblquote Oh, no \emdash  I don\rquote t like this \emdash  oh, I \i really\i0  don\rquote t like this \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry urged Buckbeak forward. They were gliding quietly toward the upper floors of the castle. \'85 Harry pulled hard on the left-hand side of the rope, and Buckbeak turned. Harry was trying to count the windows flashing past \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Whoa!\rdblquote  he said, pulling backward as hard as he could.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Buckbeak slowed down and they found themselves at a stop, un\-less you counted the fact that they kept rising up and down several feet as the hippogriff beat his wings to remain airborne.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He\rquote s there!\rdblquote  Harry said, spotting Sirius as they rose up beside the window. He reached out, and as Buckbeak\rquote s wings fell, was able to tap sharply on the glass.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Black looked up. Harry saw his jaw drop. He leapt from his chair, hurried to the window and tried to open it, but it was locked.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Stand back!\rdblquote  Hermione called to him, and she took out her wand, still gripping the back of Harry\rquote s robes with her left hand.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Alohomora\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The window sprang open.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How \emdash  how \emdash  ?\rdblquote  said Black weakly, staring at the hippogriff.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Get on \emdash  there\rquote s not much time,\rdblquote  said Harry, gripping Buck\-beak firmly on either side of his sleek neck to hold him steady. \ldblquote You\rquote ve got to get out of here \emdash  the dementors are coming \emdash  Macnair\rquote s gone to get them.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Black placed a hand on either side of the window frame and heaved his head and shoulders out of it. It was very lucky he was so thin. In seconds, he had managed to fling one leg over Buckbeak\rquote s back and pull himself onto the hippogriff behind Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Okay, Buckbeak, up!\rdblquote  said Harry, shaking the rope. \ldblquote Up to the tower \emdash  come on!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The hippogriff gave one sweep of its mighty wings and they were soaring upward again, high as the top of the West Tower. Buckbeak landed with a clatter on the battlements, and Harry and Hermione slid off him at once.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Sirius, you\rquote d better go, quick,\rdblquote  Harry panted. \ldblquote They\rquote ll reach Flitwick\rquote s office any moment, they\rquote ll find out you\rquote re gone.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Buckbeak pawed the ground, tossing his sharp head.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What happened to the other boy? Ron?\rdblquote  croaked Sirius.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He\rquote s going to be okay. He\rquote s still out of it, but Madam Pomfrey says she\rquote ll be able to make him better. Quick \emdash  go \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But Black was still staring down at Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How can I ever thank \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote GO!\rdblquote  Harry and Hermione shouted together.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Black wheeled Buckbeak around, facing the open sky.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We\rquote ll see each other again,\rdblquote  he said. \ldblquote You are \emdash  truly your fa\-ther\rquote s son, Harry. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He squeezed Buckbeak\rquote s sides with his heels. Harry and Hermione jumped back as the enormous wings rose once more. \'85 The hip\-pogriff took off into the air. \'85 He and his rider became smaller and smaller as Harry gazed after them \'85 then a cloud drifted across the moon. \'85 They were gone.\lang3081\par
