\ldblquote Harry!\rdblquote\par
Hermione was tugging at his sleeve, staring at her watch. \ldblquote We\rquote ve got exactly ten minutes to get back down to the hos\-pital wing without anybody seeing us \emdash  before Dumbledore locks the door \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Okay,\rdblquote  said Harry, wrenching his gaze from the sky, \ldblquote let\rquote s go. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They slipped through the doorway behind them and down a tightly spiraling stone staircase. As they reached the bottom of it, they heard voices. They flattened themselves against the wall and listened. It sounded like Fudge and Snape. They were walking quickly along the corridor at the foot of the staircase.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\'85 only hope Dumbledore\rquote s not going to make difficulties,\rdblquote  Snape was saying. \ldblquote The Kiss will be performed immediately?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote As soon as Macnair returns with the dementors. This whole Black affair has been highly embarrassing. I can\rquote t tell you how\lang3081  \lang1033 much I\rquote m looking forward to informing the \i Daily Prophet\i0  that we\rquote ve got him at last. \'85 I daresay they\rquote ll want to interview you, Snape \'85 and once young Harry\rquote s back in his right mind, I expect he\rquote ll want to tell the \i Prophet\i0  exactly how you saved him. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry clenched his teeth. He caught a glimpse of Snape\rquote s smirk as he and Fudge passed Harry and Hermione\rquote s hiding place. Their footsteps died away. Harry and Hermione waited a few moments to make sure they\rquote d really gone, then started to run in the opposite direction. Down one staircase, then another, along a new corridor \emdash  then they heard a cackling ahead.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Peeves\i0 !\rdblquote  Harry muttered, grabbing Hermione\rquote s wrist. \ldblquote In here!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They tore into a deserted classroom to their left just in time. Peeves seemed to be bouncing along the corridor in boisterous good spirits, laughing his head off.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, he\rquote s horrible,\rdblquote  whispered Hermione, her ear to the door. \ldblquote I bet he\rquote s all excited because the dementors are going to finish off Sirius. \'85\rdblquote  She checked her watch. \ldblquote Three minutes, Harry!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They waited until Peeves\rquote s gloating voice had faded into the dis\-tance, then slid back out of the room and broke into a run again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hermione \emdash  what\rquote ll happen \emdash  if we don\rquote t get back inside \emdash  before Dumbledore locks the door?\rdblquote  Harry panted.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I don\rquote t want to think about it!\rdblquote  Hermione moaned, checking her watch again. \ldblquote One minute!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They had reached the end of the corridor with the hospital wing entrance. \ldblquote Okay \emdash  I can hear Dumbledore,\rdblquote  said Hermione tensely. \ldblquote Come on, Harry!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They crept along the corridor. The door opened. Dumbledore\rquote s back appeared.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I am going to lock you in,\rdblquote  they heard him saying. \ldblquote It is five minutes to midnight. Miss Granger, three turns should do it. Good luck.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Dumbledore backed out of the room, closed the door, and took out his wand to magically lock it. Panicking, Harry and Hermione ran forward. Dumbledore looked up, and a wide smile appeared under the long silver mustache. \ldblquote Well?\rdblquote  he said quietly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We did it!\rdblquote  said Harry breathlessly. \ldblquote Sirius has gone, on Buck\-beak. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Dumbledore beamed at them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well done. I think\lang3081  \lang1033\emdash\rdblquote  He listened intently for any sound within the hospital wing. \ldblquote Yes, I think you\rquote ve gone too \emdash  get in\-side \emdash  I\rquote ll lock you in \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry and Hermione slipped back inside the dormitory. It was empty except for Ron, who was still lying motionless in the end bed. As the lock clicked behind them, Harry and Hermione crept back to their own beds, Hermione tucking the Time-Turner back under her robes. A moment later, Madam Pomfrey came striding back out of her office.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Did I hear the headmaster leaving? Am I allowed to look after my patients now?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She was in a very bad mood. Harry and Hermione thought it best to accept their chocolate quietly. Madam Pomfrey stood over them, making sure they ate it. But Harry could hardly swallow. He and Hermione were waiting, listening, their nerves jangling. \'85 And then, as they both took a fourth piece of chocolate from Madam Pomfrey, they heard a distant roar of fury echoing from somewhere above them. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What was that?\rdblquote  said Madam Pomfrey in alarm.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Now they could hear angry voices, growing louder and louder. Madam Pomfrey was staring at the door.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Really \emdash  they\rquote ll wake everybody up! What do they think they\rquote re doing?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry was trying to hear what the voices were saying. They were drawing nearer \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He must have Disapparated, Severus. We should have left somebody in the room with him. When this gets out \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote HE DIDN\rquote T DISAPPARATE!\rdblquote  Snape roared, now very close at hand. \ldblquote YOU CAN\rquote T APPARATE \i OR\i0  DISAPPARATE IN\-SIDE THIS CASTLE!\lang3081  \lang1033 THIS \emdash  HAS \emdash  SOMETHING \emdash  TO \emdash  DO \emdash  WITH \emdash  POTTER!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Severus \emdash  be reasonable \emdash  Harry has been locked up \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 BAM.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The door of the hospital wing burst open.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Fudge, Snape, and Dumbledore came striding into the ward. Dumbledore alone looked calm. Indeed, he looked as though he was quite enjoying himself. Fudge appeared angry. But Snape was beside himself.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote OUT WITH IT, POTTER!\rdblquote  he bellowed. \ldblquote WHAT DID YOU DO?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Professor Snape!\rdblquote  shrieked Madam Pomfrey. \ldblquote Control your\-self!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote See here, Snape, be reasonable,\rdblquote  said Fudge. \ldblquote This door\rquote s been locked, we just saw \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote THEY HELPED HIM ESCAPE, I KNOW IT!\rdblquote  Snape howled, pointing at Harry and Hermione. His face was twisted; spit was flying from his mouth.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Calm down, man!\rdblquote  Fudge barked. \ldblquote You\rquote re talking nonsense!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote YOU DON\rquote T KNOW POTTER!\rdblquote  shrieked Snape. \ldblquote HE DID IT, I KNOW HE DID IT \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That will do, Severus,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore quietly. \ldblquote Think about what you are saying. This door has been locked since I left the ward ten minutes ago. Madam Pomfrey, have these students left their beds?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Of course not!\rdblquote  said Madam Pomfrey, bristling. \ldblquote I would have heard them!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, there you have it, Severus,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore calmly. \ldblquote Unless you are suggesting that Harry and Hermione are able to be in two places at once, I\rquote m afraid I don\rquote t see any point in troubling them further.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Snape stood there, seething, staring from Fudge, who looked thoroughly shocked at his behavior, to Dumbledore, whose eyes were twinkling behind his glasses. Snape whirled about, robes swishing behind him, and stormed out of the ward.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Fellow seems quite unbalanced,\rdblquote  said Fudge, staring after him. \ldblquote I\rquote d watch out for him if I were you, Dumbledore.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, he\rquote s not unbalanced,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore quietly. \ldblquote He\rquote s just suffered a severe disappointment.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He\rquote s not the only one!\rdblquote  puffed Fudge. \ldblquote The \i Daily Prophet\rquote s\i0  go\-ing to have a field day! We had Black cornered and he slipped through our fingers yet again! All it needs now is for the story of that hippogriff\rquote s escape to get out, and I\rquote ll be a laughingstock! Well\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 I\rquote d better go and notify the Ministry. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And the dementors?\rdblquote  said Dumbledore. \ldblquote They\rquote ll be removed from the school, I trust?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh yes, they\rquote ll have to go,\rdblquote  said Fudge, running his fingers\lang3081  \lang1033 distractedly through his hair. \ldblquote Never dreamed they\rquote d attempt to ad\-minister the Kiss on an innocent boy. \'85 Completely out of con\-trol \'85 no, I\rquote ll have them packed off back to Azkaban tonight. \'85 Perhaps we should think about dragons at the school entrance. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hagrid would like that,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore, smiling at Harry and Hermione. As he and Fudge left the dormitory, Madam Pom\-frey hurried to the door and locked it again. Muttering angrily to herself, she headed back to her office.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a low moan from the other end of the ward. Ron had woken up. They could see him sitting up, rubbing his head, look\-ing around.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What \emdash  what happened?\rdblquote  he groaned. \ldblquote Harry? Why are we in here? Where\rquote s Sirius? Where\rquote s Lupin? What\rquote s going on?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry and Hermione looked at each other.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You explain,\rdblquote  said Harry, helping himself to some more choco\-late.\lang3081\par
\par
\lang1033 When Harry, Ron, and Hermione left the hospital wing at noon the next day, it was to find an almost deserted castle. The swelter\-ing heat and the end of the exams meant that everyone was taking full advantage of another Hogsmeade visit. Neither Ron nor Hermione felt like going, however, so they and Harry wandered onto the grounds, still talking about the extraordinary events of the previous night and wondering where Sirius and Buckbeak were now. Sitting near the lake, watching the giant squid waving its ten\-tacles lazily above the water, Harry lost the thread of the conversa\-tion as he looked across to the opposite bank. The stag had galloped toward him from there just last night. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A shadow fell across them and they looked up to see a very bleary-eyed Hagrid, mopping his sweaty face with one of his table\-cloth-sized handkerchiefs and beaming down at them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Know I shouldn\rquote  feel happy, after wha\rquote  happened las\rquote  night,\rdblquote  he said. \ldblquote I mean, Black escapin\rquote  again, an\rquote  everythin\rquote  \emdash  but guess what?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What?\rdblquote  they said, pretending to look curious.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Beaky! He escaped! He\rquote s free! Bin celebratin\rquote  all night!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That\rquote s wonderful!\rdblquote  said Hermione, giving Ron a reproving look because he looked as though he was close to laughing.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah \'85 can\rquote t\rquote ve tied him up properly,\rdblquote  said Hagrid, gazing happily out over the grounds. \ldblquote I was worried this mornin\rquote , mind \'85 thought he mighta met Professor Lupin on the grounds, but Lupin says he never ate anythin\rquote  las\rquote  night. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What?\rdblquote  said Harry quickly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Blimey, haven\rquote  yeh heard?\rdblquote  said Hagrid, his smile fading a little. He lowered his voice, even though there was nobody in sight. \ldblquote Er \emdash  Snape told all the Slytherins this mornin\rquote . \'85\lang3081  \lang1033 Thought everyone\rquote d know by now \'85 Professor Lupin\rquote s a werewolf, see. An\rquote  he was loose on the grounds las\rquote  night. \'85 He\rquote s packin\rquote  now, o\rquote  course.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He\rquote s\lang3081  \lang1033\i packing\i0 ?\rdblquote  said Harry, alarmed. \ldblquote Why?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Leavin\rquote , isn\rquote  he?\rdblquote  said Hagrid, looking surprised that Harry had to ask. \ldblquote Resigned firs\rquote  thing this mornin\rquote . Says he can\rquote t risk it hap\-penin\rquote  again.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry scrambled to his feet.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m going to see him,\rdblquote  he said to Ron and Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But if he\rquote s resigned \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\emdash  doesn\rquote t sound like there\rquote s anything we can do \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I don\rquote t care. I still want to see him. I\rquote ll meet you back here.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\par
\lang1033 Lupin\rquote s office door was open. He had already packed most of his things. The grindylow\rquote s empty tank stood next to his battered old suitcase, which was open and nearly full. Lupin was bending over something on his desk and looked up only when Harry knocked on the door.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I saw you coming,\rdblquote  said Lupin, smiling. He pointed to the parchment he had been poring over. It was the Marauder\rquote s Map.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I just saw Hagrid,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote And he said you\rquote d resigned. It\rquote s not true, is it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m afraid it is,\rdblquote  said Lupin. He started opening his desk draw\-ers and taking out the contents.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Why\i0 ?\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote The Ministry of Magic don\rquote t think you were helping Sirius, do they?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Lupin crossed to the door and closed it behind Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No. Professor Dumbledore managed to convince Fudge that I was trying to save your lives.\rdblquote  He sighed. \ldblquote That was the final straw for Severus. I think the loss of the Order of Merlin hit him hard. So he \emdash  er \emdash  \i accidentally\i0  let slip that I am a werewolf this morning at breakfast.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote re not leaving just because of that!\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Lupin smiled wryly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote This time tomorrow, the owls will start arriving from par\-ents. \'85 They will not want a werewolf teaching their children, Harry. And after last night, I see their point. I could have bitten any of you. \'85 That must never happen again.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote re the best Defense Against the Dark Arts teacher we\rquote ve ever had!\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote Don\rquote t go!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Lupin shook his head and didn\rquote t speak. He carried on emptying his drawers. Then, while Harry was trying to think of a good argu\-ment to make him stay, Lupin said, \ldblquote From what the headmaster told me this morning, you saved a lot of lives last night, Harry. If I\rquote m proud of anything I\rquote ve done this year, it\rquote s how much you\rquote ve learned. \'85 Tell me about your Patronus.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How d\rquote you know about that?\rdblquote  said Harry, distracted.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What else could have driven the dementors back?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry told Lupin what had happened. When he\rquote d finished, Lupin was smiling again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes, your father was always a stag when he transformed,\rdblquote  he said. \ldblquote You guessed right \'85 that\rquote s why we called him Prongs.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Lupin threw his last few books into his case, closed the desk drawers, and turned to look at Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Here \emdash  I brought this from the Shrieking Shack last night,\rdblquote  he said, handing Harry back the Invisibility Cloak. \ldblquote And \'85\rdblquote  He hes\-itated, then held out the Marauder\rquote s Map too. \ldblquote I am no longer your teacher, so I don\rquote t feel guilty about giving you back this as well. It\rquote s no use to me, and I daresay you, Ron, and Hermione will find uses for it.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry took the map and grinned.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You told me Moony, Wormtail, Padfoot, and Prongs would\rquote ve wanted to lure me out of school\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 you said they\rquote d have thought it was funny.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And so we would have,\rdblquote  said Lupin, now reaching down to close his case. \ldblquote I have no hesitation in saying that James would have\lang3081  \lang1033 been highly disappointed if his son had never found any of the se\-cret passages out of the castle.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a knock on the door. Harry hastily stuffed the Ma\-rauder\rquote s Map and the Invisibility Cloak into his pocket.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It was Professor Dumbledore. He didn\rquote t look surprised to see Harry there.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Your carriage is at the gates, Remus,\rdblquote  he said.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Thank you, Headmaster.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Lupin picked up his old suitcase and the empty grindylow tank.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well \emdash  good-bye, Harry,\rdblquote  he said, smiling. \ldblquote It has been a real pleasure teaching you. I feel sure we\rquote ll meet again some\-time. Headmaster, there is no need to see me to the gates, I can manage. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
