\lang1033\ldblquote It does not,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore quietly. \ldblquote Hasn\rquote t your experience with the Time-Turner taught you anything, Harry? The conse\-quences of our actions are always so complicated, so diverse, that predicting the future is a very difficult business indeed. \'85 Profes\-sor Trelawney, bless her, is living proof of that. \'85 You did a very noble thing, in saving Pettigrew\rquote s life.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
