\lang1033\ldblquote An easy mistake to make,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore softly. \ldblquote I expect you\rquote ll tire of hearing it, but you do look \i extraordinarily\i0  like James. Except for the eyes \'85 you have your mother\rquote s eyes.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry shook his head.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It was stupid, thinking it was him,\rdblquote  he muttered. \ldblquote I mean, I knew he was dead.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You think the dead we loved ever truly leave us? You think that we don\rquote t recall them more clearly than ever in times of great trou\-ble? Your father is alive in you, Harry, and shows himself most\lang3081  \lang1033 plainly when you have need of him. How else could you produce that \i particular\i0  Patronus? Prongs rode again last night.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It took a moment for Harry to realize what Dumbledore had said.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Last night Sirius told me all about how they became Animagi,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore, smiling. \ldblquote An extraordinary achievement \emdash  not least, keeping it quiet from me. And then I remembered the most unusual form your Patronus took, when it charged Mr. Malfoy down at your Quidditch match against Ravenclaw. You know, Harry, in a way, you did see your father last night. \'85 You found him inside yourself.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And Dumbledore left the office, leaving Harry to his very con\-fused thoughts.\lang3081\par
\par
\lang1033 Nobody at Hogwarts now knew the truth of what had happened the night that Sirius, Buckbeak, and Pettigrew had vanished except Harry, Ron, Hermione, and Professor Dumbledore. As the end of term approached, Harry heard many different theories about what had really happened, but none of them came close to the truth.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Malfoy was furious about Buckbeak. He was convinced that Hagrid had found a way of smuggling the hippogriff to safety, and seemed outraged that he and his father had been outwitted by a gamekeeper. Percy Weasley, meanwhile, had much to say on the subject of Sirius\rquote s escape.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote If I manage to get into the Ministry, I\rquote ll have a lot of proposals to make about Magical Law Enforcement!\rdblquote  he told the only person who would listen \emdash  his girlfriend, Penelope.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Though the weather was perfect, though the atmosphere was so\lang3081  \lang1033 cheerful, though he knew they had achieved the near impossible in helping Sirius to freedom, Harry had never approached the end of a school year in worse spirits.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He certainly wasn\rquote t the only one who was sorry to see Professor Lupin go. The whole of Harry\rquote s Defense Against the Dark Arts class was miserable about his resignation.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Wonder what they\rquote ll give us next year?\rdblquote  said Seamus Finnigan gloomily.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Maybe a vampire,\rdblquote  suggested Dean Thomas hopefully.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It wasn\rquote t only Professor Lupin\rquote s departure that was weighing on Harry\rquote s mind. He couldn\rquote t help thinking a lot about Professor Trelawney\rquote s prediction. He kept wondering where Pettigrew was now, whether he had sought sanctuary with Voldemort yet. But the thing that was lowering Harry\rquote s spirits most of all was the prospect of re\-turning to the Dursleys. For maybe half an hour, a glorious half hour, he had believed he would be living with Sirius from now on \'85 his parents\rquote  best friend. \'85 It would have been the next best thing to hav\-ing his own father back. And while no news of Sirius was definitely good news, because it meant he had successfully gone into hiding, Harry couldn\rquote t help feeling miserable when he thought of the home he might have had, and the fact that it was now impossible.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The exam results came out on the last day of term. Harry, Ron, and Hermione had passed every subject. Harry was amazed that he had got through Potions. He had a shrewd suspicion that Dumble\-dore might have stepped in to stop Snape failing him on purpose. Snape\rquote s behavior toward Harry over the past week had been quite alarming. Harry wouldn\rquote t have thought it possible that Snape\rquote s dislike for him could increase, but it certainly had. A muscle\lang3081  \lang1033 twitched unpleasantly at the corner of Snape\rquote s thin mouth every time he looked at Harry, and he was constantly flexing his fingers, as though itching to place them around Harry\rquote s throat.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Percy had got his top-grade N.E.W.T.s; Fred and George had scraped a handful of O.W.L.s each. Gryffindor House, meanwhile, largely thanks to their spectacular performance in the Quidditch Cup, had won the House championship for the third year running. This meant that the end of term feast took place amid decorations of scarlet and gold, and that the Gryffindor table was the noisiest of the lot, as everybody celebrated. Even Harry managed to forget about the journey back to the Dursleys the next day as he ate, drank, talked, and laughed with the rest.\lang3081\par
\par
\lang1033 As the Hogwarts Express pulled out of the station the next morn\-ing, Hermione gave Harry and Ron some surprising news.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I went to see Professor McGonagall this morning, just before breakfast. I\rquote ve decided to drop Muggle Studies.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But you passed your exam with three hundred and twenty per\-cent!\rdblquote  said Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I know,\rdblquote  sighed Hermione, \ldblquote but I can\rquote t stand another year like this one. That Time-Turner, it was driving me mad. I\rquote ve handed it in. Without Muggle Studies and Divination, I\rquote ll be able to have a normal schedule again.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I still can\rquote t \i believe\i0  you didn\rquote t tell us about it,\rdblquote  said Ron grumpily. \ldblquote We\rquote re supposed to be your \i friends.\i0\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I promised I wouldn\rquote t tell \i anyone,\i0\rdblquote  said Hermione severely. She looked around at Harry, who was watching Hogwarts disappear from view behind a mountain. Two whole months before he\rquote d see it again. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, cheer up, Harry!\rdblquote  said Hermione sadly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m okay,\rdblquote  said Harry quickly. \ldblquote Just thinking about the holi\-days.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, I\rquote ve been thinking about them too,\rdblquote  said Ron. \ldblquote Harry, you\rquote ve got to come and stay with us. I\rquote ll fix it up with Mum and Dad, then I\rquote ll call you. I know how to use a fellytone now \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote A \i telephone,\i0  Ron,\rdblquote  said Hermione. \ldblquote Honestly, \i you\i0  should take Muggle Studies next year. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron ignored her.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s the Quidditch World Cup this summer! How about it, Harry? Come and stay, and we\rquote ll go and see it! Dad can usually get tickets from work.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
